snippet.textDisplay: Comparing the coverage of royal women is an exercise in futility, but were one to weigh the number of disparaging articles against the number of Palace rebuttals, the results would clearly illustrate how rarely they push back. People have been quick to point out Kensington Palace's strenuous denials over Kate reportedly getting Botox. Aides delivered the rebuke because Dr. Munir Somji, a plastic surgeon, was attempting to capitalise on the Duchess by suggesting she was one of his patients. The Palace's carefully-worded statement noted the Royal Family never endorses commercial activities, but it didn't directly confirm or deny the claim Kate had had work. It represented a classic example of the Palace protecting the institution as opposed to one of its members. The majority of reasonably minded people would agree the trivial nature of Botox doesn't come close to a baby being compared to a chimpanzee. There's no justification, no worthy excuse and such a comparison barely dignifies a response, but the lack of response cut deeply for a broad cross-section of society as it must have for Harry and Meghan. In my opinion: More should have been done to protect Meghan, but as history has shown, when the royals intervene, negative coverage has a tendency to escalate. In this instance, however, the royals' self-imposed silence had the exact same effect. it obvious why the Duke and Duchess of Sussex choose to quit from it all, even if it was a shocking and bold move to make. If your boss (aka the taxpayer) bully you every single day 24/7 you would quit your job too.

snippet.textDisplay: This is a shocking thing to say - but this is not typical AT ALL - the British public does not talk like this about her. This is an Americanism - we dont have "trailer trash" per se in the UK. So this expression was taken from the American language. It's a revolting way to speak about anyone. The British public was immensely critical of this woman as we were about the idiot who called Archie something derogatory. I dont particularly like how MM has gone about her business in the Royal Family. I have NEVER heard anything racist said about her in my every day life. But I have heard criticism. And criticism about Harry also. There seems to be a sector that have equated criticism with racism - how does that tie in to criticism about Harry - do we have to call it Gingerism???? Which is ridiculous if course - but so is this constant call of racism. We criticised Diana; Sarah; Catherine; Camilla but this seems to be overlooked - no calls of racism there. Princess Angela was the first woman of colour to marry into a reigning European dynasty - no calls of racism being pointed at her marital family. So .... I condemn anyone that speaks in such a derogatory way about anyone - especially a woman about another woman.  But check out the way the MM supporters are speaking about members of the royal family. Citing that they should be killed - it goes both ways. MM and any woman or man who marries a senior working royal will be criticised. It's probably a damned if you do damned if you dont kind of life. I personally wouldn't want it. But anyone in public life opens themselves up to be criticised- I've heard woman of colour slagging off other woman of colour on American TV. Racism is everywhere - and I dont support it. But I am so tired of the finger of racism being pointed towards any criticism that is levelled at MM. I'm in the ground living life with normal, British folks of all nationalities and not ONCE  have I heard ANY racist comment being directed towards MM.
